// Save to ~/.claude/settings.json
// Remove ALL lines starting with // before saving — Claude Code uses strict
// JSON and will silently fall back to the real Anthropic API if comments remain.
//
// ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL — gateway root, no trailing /v1.
// ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN — sent as Authorization: Bearer. Set to KIRO_GATEWAY_API_KEY.
//   Keep ANTHROPIC_API_KEY unset or Claude Code routes to the real Anthropic API.
// ANTHROPIC_SMALL_FAST_MODEL — model Claude Code uses for background tasks (title
//   generation, short summaries). Must be set to a model the gateway serves.
//   Without it Claude Code defaults to claude-haiku-4-5 which the gateway
//   doesn't have, causing background tasks to fail silently.
//   ANTHROPIC_MODEL is not needed — Claude Code's own default (claude-sonnet-4-6)
//   is served by the gateway, and CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_GATEWAY_MODEL_DISCOVERY lets
//   you pick any model via /model at runtime anyway.
// CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS — required. Claude Code 2.x sends extra
//   beta headers (context_management etc) that cause 400 errors on third-party
//   gateways. This suppresses them.
// CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_GATEWAY_MODEL_DISCOVERY — auto-populates the /model picker
//   with all models from GET /v1/models at startup. No need to list every model
//   in settings.json — just enable this flag (requires Claude Code v2.1.129+).
{
  "env": {
    "ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL": "http://127.0.0.1:8000",
    "ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN": "change-me",
    "ANTHROPIC_SMALL_FAST_MODEL": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
    "CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS": "1",
    "CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_GATEWAY_MODEL_DISCOVERY": "1"
  }
}
